from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier
import plotly.graph_objs as go 
from plotly import tools

# Assuming the target variable is in the 'target' column
X = data.drop('raisedhands', axis=1)  # Features
y = data['Class']  # Target variable



# Assuming 'X' is a pandas DataFrame containing your features
X_encoded = pd.get_dummies(X)

# Assuming 'y' is a pandas Series containing your labels
y_encoded = pd.get_dummies(y)

# Now you can proceed with splitting the data and fitting the classifier
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X_encoded, y_encoded, test_size=0.5, random_state=82)
model = DecisionTreeClassifier()
model.fit(X_train, y_train)
# Previous code for fitting the model

y_pred = model.predict(X_test)  # Generate predictions on the test data

accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)  # Calculate the accuracy score


print("x train data", X_train)
print("y train data", y_train)
print("x test data", X_test)
print("y test data",y_test)

print("Accuracy:", accuracy)
